<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="834" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14052b.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-23T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>By direction of the President I send the following to be communicated by
                            you to Villa at once.</p>
                        <p>[The remainder is identical with that of the foregoing telegram to Mr.
                            Silliman.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>